.TH AGENTSANDBOX 1 "2026-04-29" "agentsandbox" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
agentsandbox \- secure, reproducible NixOS Linux VM for agentic workflows
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B agentsandbox
[\fIglobal-options\fR] \fIcommand\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
agentsandbox manages per-workspace Linux VMs built from NixOS templates.
It also provides convenience commands to control libvirt domains, mount
host paths into a running guest, and attach via SSH.

Some subcommands are listed in the CLI but are not yet wired to the
runtime (they may print a generic "Comming soon(tm)..." message). See
each command's section for the current status.
.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
.TP
.B -g , --global
Use the global sandbox scope instead of resolving the active workspace's
local \fI\&.agentsandbox\fR.
.TP
.B -n , --hostname HOSTNAME
Select sandbox hostname.
.RI (Default: default)
.TP
.B -w , --workspace PATH
Resolve the active workspace and config as if running from this directory.
.RI (Default: current directory)
.br
This affects how \fI\&.agentsandbox\fR is resolved.
.SH COMMANDS
.SS version
Print the version.

Alias: none.
.TP
.BI agentsandbox version
.SS doctor
Show diagnostics (resolved config/instance paths, relevant host commands).
.TP
.BI agentsandbox doctor
.SS init
Create \fI\&.agentsandbox/\fR and write the initial template files.
.TP
.BI agentsandbox init
.BR -f , --force
Overwrite existing files.
.SS build
Build the guest system from the template-based system profile.
.TP
.BI agentsandbox build
.BR -b , --bootstrap
Build the initial template-based system profile instead.
.br
Current configs are kept.
.SS up
Rebuild and start a VM.
.TP
.BI agentsandbox up
.BR -d , --detach
Detach after starting.
.br
If the VM is already running, it rebuilds and proceeds to the next steps.
.SS down
Tear down the VM gracefully.
.TP
.BI agentsandbox down
.SS kill
Forcibly stop the VM and delete guest files selected by destroy flags
via \fBdestroy\fR.
.TP
.BI agentsandbox kill
.SS destroy
Kill and delete guest files selected by flags (none by default).
.br
For the non-project instance, use \fB\-\-global\fR.
.TP
.BI agentsandbox destroy
.BR -s , --system
Remove sysroot.
.TP
.BR -d , --data
Remove persistent data.
.TP
.BR -l , --logs
Remove the instance states such as logs.
.TP
.BR -c , --conf
Remove the resolved config dir.
.br
Note: command has alias \fBdestory\fR.
.SS pause
Pause running VMs for all hostnames in the current config.
.TP
.BI agentsandbox pause
.SS unpause
Unpause VMs for all hostnames in the current config.
.TP
.BI agentsandbox unpause
.SS ps
List VM statuses for all hostnames in the current config.
.TP
.BI agentsandbox ps
.SS ssh
Run a command as a user in a running VM, or attach if omitted.
.TP
.BI agentsandbox ssh
[\fIargs\fR...]
.br
The SSH port is selected from the guest's \fIport-forwards\fR configuration.
.SS exec
Run a command as root in a running VM, or attach if omitted.
.TP
.BI agentsandbox exec
[\fIargs\fR...]
.br
The SSH port is selected from the guest's \fIport-forwards\fR configuration.
.SS logs
Show logs from a running VM.
.TP
.BI agentsandbox logs
[\fIargs\fR...]
.br
By default, runs journalctl with \fB\-en1000\fR and then applies extra args.
.SS stats
Display percentage of CPU, memory, network I/O, block I/O and PIDs for VMs.
.TP
.BI agentsandbox stats
.SS wait
Block until the VM becomes one of the given states.
.TP
.BI agentsandbox wait
[\fIstates\fR...]
.br
Wait for stop states by default.
.br
Default states:
.nf
down, shut off, crashed
.fi
.SS mount
Mount a file or directory into a running VM, or show mounts entries.
.TP
.BI agentsandbox mount
[\fIpath\fR] [\fIname\fR]
.br
If \fIpath\fR and \fIname\fR are omitted, it prints the current \fImounts\fR
entries from the resolved config.
.SS unmount
Unmount a file or directory from a running VM now and on future starts.
.TP
.BI agentsandbox unmount
\fIpath\fR
.SS port
Print the public port for a port binding.
.TP
.BI agentsandbox port
[\fIguest_port\fR] [\fIguest_proto\fR]
.br
Status: CLI entry exists, but runtime dispatch is not wired yet.
.SS allow-domain
Add a firewall rule that allows outbound traffic to a domain.
.TP
.BI agentsandbox allow-domain
\fIdomain\fR
.br
Status: CLI entry exists, but runtime dispatch is not wired yet.
.SS unallow-domain
Remove the rule for the domain.
.TP
.BI agentsandbox unallow-domain
\fIdomain\fR
.br
Status: CLI entry exists, but runtime dispatch is not wired yet.
.SS proxy-logs
Follow MITM proxy logs.
.TP
.BI agentsandbox proxy-logs
.br
Status: CLI entry exists, but runtime dispatch is not wired yet.
.SS verify
Verify and repair build.
.TP
.BI agentsandbox verify
.br
Behavior:
.br
1) Uses host \fBnix-store\fR to run verify/repair against the guest store.
.br
2) If the guest is running, runs \fBnixos-rebuild --repair\fR inside the guest.
.br
Limitations:
.br
It uses the host \fBnix\fR and related tools for store verification/repair.
.br
It does not analyze malicious \fBflake.nix\fR or other executables.
.SH FILES
.TP
\fI\&.agentsandbox/\fR
Local config root created by \fBinit\fR when not using \fB\-\-global\fR.
.TP
.nf
mounts
allowed_hosts
flake.nix
configuration.nix
.fi
Template files written under the resolved config directory.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
0
Success.
.TP
1
Failure (errors are printed to stderr).
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Build and start:
.nf
agentsandbox build
agentsandbox up
.fi
.TP
Mount a workspace subpath into the guest:
.nf
agentsandbox mount ./alpha my-alpha
.fi
.TP
Run a command in the guest:
.nf
agentsandbox ssh -- uname -a
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
virsh(1), ssh(1), journalctl(1), nixos-rebuild(8)
